
DISCOM Test Utility for R-Car Gen3 based platforms

Description
===========

  discom_test is a test utility of DISCOM feature in libWFD library. Given an input JPEG/PNG image, the program will 
  decompress the image to RGBX8888 raw data, then calculate CRC32 value of raw data using CRC polynomial algorithm from 
  IEEE-802.3. After that, this CRC32 value will be compared with CRC32 calculated from DISCOM module. This program use 
  QNX libimg to decompress JPEG/PNG image. Please configure system to support libimg before running this program.

Options
=======
  --display -d
    Screen display ID of monitor that will be tested.

  --image -i
    Path of the image that will be calculated CRC32 (*.jpg, *.jpeg, *.png is accepted). Displayed position is fixed
    to upper left corner. 

  --attach -a
    DISCOM position in VSP2 graphic pipeline. There are two possible values of attached position:
      + input  : RPF->UIF->BRU (default)
      + output : RPF->BRU->UIF

  --rect -r
    Image ROI that will be calculated CRC32
      + If attach type is input, default ROI is entire given image
      + If attach type is output, default ROI is entire image that being displayed on monitor

Example
=======
  1) Calculate CRC32 in case Image->RPF->UIF->BRU
     $ discom_test --display=1 --image=/tmp/sample.jpg

  2) Calculate CRC32 in case Sub-Image->RPF->UIF->BRU
     $ discom_test --display=1 --image=/tmp/sample.jpg --rect=100,100,500,500

  3) Calculate CRC32 in case Image->RPF->BRU->UIF
     $ discom_test --display=1 --image=/tmp/sample.jpg --rect=0,0,1280,720 --attach=output 
